  <prompt>
    Add an optional `loadNotificationContext?: () => Promise&lt;NarrateRequest | null&gt;` factory option to the existing Daily Briefing section registration. When the option is omitted, behavior matches the empty-payload contract today (UI renders empty state, BFF returns empty bullets). When the option is provided, the value is invoked to obtain the per-user notification context that gets passed to BFF `/narrate`. This is the injection seam that P2 will preserve when the registration moves to the new shared package.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in React 19, Fluent UI v9, and the SpaarkeAi workspace section-registration pattern.</role>

  <goal>The dailyBriefingRegistration factory signature accepts `loadNotificationContext` as an optional option; existing standalone code page consumers continue to work unchanged; the registration is ready for SpaarkeAi `main.tsx` to inject `loadSpaarkeAiNotificationContext` (task 002).</goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-01: SpaarkeAi workspace pane currently renders empty Daily Briefing despite users having unread notifications because `loadSpaarkeAiNotificationContext` has no injection seam. Adding the factory option closes the seam without breaking the standalone code page (which omits the option).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/sections/dailyBriefing/dailyBriefingRegistration.ts</file>
